    <head>
        <meta name="keyword" content="java, mercurial" />
    </head>
    <body>
        <section name="Introduction">
            <subsection name="Aims">                
                <p>
                    HgKit aims to be a pure Java implementation of
                    <a href="http://www.selenic.com/mercurial/wiki/">Mercurial</a>
                    , an advanced
                    <a
                        href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Revision_control#Distributed_revision_control">distributed revision control
                        system</a>
                    .
                </p>
                <p>
                    This project aims to replace most of the native
                    invocations of Mercurial in e.g. the
                    <a href="http://trac-hg.assembla.com/mercurialeclipse">Mercurial Eclipse Plugin</a>
                    .
                </p>
            </subsection>
            <subsection name="Files">
                <p>
                    Current snapshots may be downloaded from
                    <a
                        href="http://hgkit.berlios.de/maven2snapshotrepo/de/berlios/hgkit/hgkit/">Berlios</a>
                    .
                </p>
            </subsection>
            <subsection name="Development">
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        Make sure you have the
                        <code>hg</code>
                        -Binary in your
                        <code>PATH</code>
                        .
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Before editing code, please import
                        <a
                            href="http://hg.berlios.de/repos/hgkit/raw-file/tip/eclipse-codetemplates.xml">codetemplates</a>
                        and <a href="http://hg.berlios.de/repos/hgkit//raw-file/tip/eclipse-format.xml">format</a> XML files.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </subsection>
            <subsection name="Build Status">
                <script type="text/javascript" src="images/hudson_widget.js"></script>
            </subsection>
        </section>
    </body>
